  "soap_summary": "Adult with several-day history of sore, red, very itchy rash primarily on chest (also hands/arms/armpits/back reported elsewhere). Background of eczema; clinician considers this likely an eczema flare. Symptoms: intense pruritus causing sleep disturbance, some skin cracking and pain. No fever, no cough or breathing difficulty, no pus/bleeding. Past asthma resolved. Patient tried OTC topical steroid last night and has tried antihistamines recently without benefit. Plan: prescribe a stronger topical steroid and emollients for 7\u201310 days, consider/offer OTC antihistamines (loratadine or chlorphenamine), keep trigger diary and review if no improvement.",
